      "value": "Breach deals damage with heavy weapons."
    },
    "description": "<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Requirements:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">you must have mastered one or more Classes among </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Darkblade</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">, </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fury</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">, and </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Weaponmaster</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">After you hit a creature with </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Breach</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">, if you attacked with a </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">melee </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">weapon that belongs to the </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">heavy </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Category, you may have the attack deal damage equal to your </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>High Roll (HR)</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">instead of dealing no damage. Any source of extra damage, including the extra damage from the third option of the Breach Skill itself, still applies — ignore the damage dealt by the weapon.</span> </p>",
